name: "Comfortable 55m2 Apartment"
description: The modern equiped Apartment is located in Döbling, one of the nicest districts. The unique location of the apartment you are able to reach the center of Vienna with famous landmarks such as the Stephansdom or Vienna city hall within 15 minutes.
neighborhood_overview:
The Apartment is located in Döbling, the 19th district of Vienna. Parts of Döbling such as Grinzing are very popular for tourists. Furthermore, there are lots of residences of foreign diplomats.

The unique location of the apartment you are able to reach the center of Vienna with famous landmarks such as the Stephansdom, Vienna city hall, Austrian parliament and the Hofburg within 15 minutes using public transportation (tram lines 37, 38 & D as well as close by subway stations Spittelau (U4 & U6) and Nußdorf (U6). The beautiful, quiet vineyards are also very close.

In case you arrive by car, you do not need parking tickets in most parts of Döbling – unlike in most other districts.
host_about:

name: Central & childfriendly in a beautiful district
description:
We are a young family from Vienna and rent out a newly refurbished (May 2015) apartment 51m2 with old wooden floors in a building from 1913.
We speak English, Spanish, French, German and Dutch and love hosting so many different people from all over the world!
neighborhood_overview:
The 8th district is a well-to-do but also young residential area with lots of nice cafes, restaurants, bars, theatres, shops and parcs.
The apartment is perfectly situated in the heart of the Josefstadt and within walking distance you reach the City Hall (10min), Parliament (15min), Burg Theater (10min), the University of Vienna (15min), the city centre (15-30min).
Walking out of the city (15min) you can discover the up-and-coming Yppenplatz in Ottakring (16th disrtict) with ist wonderful market, trendy cafes and restaurants.
We have prepared a small booklet for you with recommendations for restaurants, sightseeing, cultural events and nice day trips.
The lovely 7th district lies also within walking distance (15min).
The "Altes AKH" hosting the University of Vienna and a large park often hosting cultural events lies within 10min walk.
The largest hospital in Austria, the Allgemeine Krankenhaus AKH, is also closeby (20min walk).
host_about:
Hallo!

We are Miriam & Philipp, two Viennese by heart. 
We grew up in Vienna and live here now with our two daughters: we love to live here and think it's a great place to visit!

Philipp is a graphic designer and illustrator and Miriam just started her own company "in love with paper" designing notebooks, blankish books and friendship books for adults, made of upcycling- and designpapers, produced in Vienna and surroundings.

We both love to travel and meet people from around the world. 
Since we are currently travelling less, we love that the world comes to us!

We are interested in people, arts, culture, music and movies.

We enjoy life: come visit!

"Wir leben alle unter dem gleichen Himmel, aber wir haben nicht alle den gleichen Horizont."

Ihr bekommt bei uns nicht nur ein gemütliches, neu eingerichtetes Apartment zu fairem Preis, wir sind sogar für Euch persönlich anzutreffen. Jeden Tag von 6:00 bis 22:00 Uhr... Wir freuen uns auf Euch und würden Euch gerne eine tolle Zeit in Wien bereiten.

name: Romantic & silent viennese apartment, near center
description: This 55 sqm large apartment is located in a low-traffic area with good infrastructure, in only 15 minutes you're able to reach the very city center of Vienna with all its famous historical spots of this wonderful metropole. You even get quick and easy to the former Habsburger summer residence, the castle of Schönbrunn or to the forests of Vienna to relax or do sports. The "Brunnenmarkt", Europe’s longest street market, is within easy reach. The 10er Marie, Vienna's oldest Heuriger is nearby.
neighborhood_overview:
There are several supermarkets, restaurants, snack bars and shops as well as numerous idyllic "Heurigen" where the original Viennese tradition is still alive. One noteworthy example is 10er Marie, Vienna's oldest "Heurigen" which is classified as an historical monument.
The nearby Vienna Woods offer you seemingly endless opportunities for walks, hikes and mountain biking.
The "Brunnenmarkt", Europe’s longest street market, is within easy reach. The Viennese enjoy having lunch or sipping their coffee in the atmosphere of this nice old area with its many restaurants and snack bars.
The recreation area "Steinhofgründe" and "Otto Wagner Kirche" are only a short bus ride away.

neighborhood_overview:
The flat lies in an amazing location. Right next to Vienna’s biggest park, the Prater, and also perfectly connected through its own U2 metro station, Krieau. The result: it lets you live and work in the green surroundings of 1020 Vienna, while being just a few minutes from Stephansplatz in the heart of Vienna.

In short walking distance: supermarkets, bakery, pharmacy, ATM

Not only is the Prater Vienna’s green oasis but it also offers the possibility to practise a wide range of sports. Whether cycling, running, skating or yoga - there’s something here for everyone. Expansive meadows, city hiking trails, woods and bodies of water - nature pulsates in the Prater all around the 4.5 kilometre-long main promenade. The ‘Hauptallee’, where cyclists, joggers, horse-drawn carriages and skaters are to be found, is lined by 2,500 trees. No other part of the city has a much green space as the Prater.

There is also the largest market in Vienna, the fountain market with its colourful stalls. The market flows into Yppen Platz, which enjoys great popularity and hosts a number of coffees and pubs.

The 7th district - called a new building - is located above the belt. This hip neighborhood not only houses the city's best bars and scene pubs, it is also known for its fashion and art scene. Here you will find exclusive clothes but also second hand, as well as antique furniture and jewellery, paired with modern designs and unusual shops and cafes.

host_about:
About me... I am an adventurous and positive person. To learn from others and see the world in new perspectives makes me grow as a person and I enjoy doing that a lot. I try to live day by day as much as it's possible, and for now I really like that way to live.

I can spend hours getting to know a person by having random conversations and listen to their stories. That could be anything from everyday life stories, long and deep conversations about life, sharing thoughts and emotions,... let's find out what we have to share with each other, plant seeds and let them grow ;)

Seeing the world in a positive way already helped me out a lot in different situations on my way.

- please smile for a second - doesn't it feel great! -

Freediving | conversations | culture and language exchanges | (acro)yoga | music | nature | broccoli | rocks | water | laughing | cooking sessions | .....

name: Cozy, inexpensive Apartment for 2
description: This cozy 30 sqm apartment is located in a low-traffic area with good infrastructure, in only 15 minutes you're able to reach the very city center of Vienna with all its famous historical spots of this wonderful metropole. You even get quick and easy to the former Habsburger summer residence, the castle of Schönbrunn or to the forests of Vienna to relax or do sports. The "Brunnenmarkt", Europe’s longest street market, is within easy reach. The 10er Marie, Vienna's oldest Heuriger is nearby.
neighborhood_overview:
There are several supermarkets, restaurants, snack bars and shops as well as numerous idyllic "Heurigen" where the original Viennese tradition is still alive. One noteworthy example is 10er Marie, Vienna's oldest "Heurigen" which is classified as an historical monument.
The nearby Vienna Woods offer you seemingly endless opportunities for walks, hikes and mountain biking.
The "Brunnenmarkt", Europe’s longest street market, is within easy reach. The Viennese enjoy having lunch or sipping their coffee in the atmosphere of this nice old area with its many restaurants and snack bars.
The recreation area "Steinhofgründe" and "Otto Wagner Kirche" are only a short bus ride away.

name: Light Flooded Roof Top Apartment with Terrace!
description:
Welcome to our place, we love it and hope you'll love it too.

With its bright windows overlooking the diverse rooftops of Vienna our apartment has a liberating urban vibe to it.
There is a spacious terrace oasis on top of it to sunbathe, relax, have a coffee or sunset drink and take in the view of Vienna.

The apartment is brand-new with beautiful oakwood floors.
It is clean, quiet, peaceful and furnished with care and love.

We hope to make your stay in Vienna comfortable and unforgettable.
neighborhood_overview:
The apartment is centrally located in walking distance to the Westbahnhof Train Station, the famous Schönbrunn Palace and Viennas biggest shopping street Mariahilferstraße.
The 15th district Rudolfsheim is an up and coming neighbourhood full of artists and young families.
There are cute little art shops in Reindorfgasse, restaurants, coffee shops (including Gota, who are well deservedly Austria’s Barista Champions of 2019) and the historical Raimundtheater just around the corner.
There are plenty of grocery shops around, the closest one is a Spar just 1 min away on the next street corner.
At the train station Westbahnhof nearby there is a shopping mall with a Merkur that is open until 11pm including Sundays (unlike most other shops in the city) and our beloved O’mellis Juice Shop with fresh healthy juices and smoothies, which is open every day too until 9.
You are also just 20 minutes from the city center with public traffic, and a half hour car ride from the
host_about:
My husband Max and I are an international couple who travels a lot, due to our professions and family life. Max is a US filmmaker and I am an actor and singer from Vienna, Austria. 
We love seeing the world and cherish places with good taste and energy, which is what we would like to offer to our guests.
We love the thought of opening our apartment to people from all over the world while we are gone. And to give them a chance to have a comfortable place while exploring the city we love so much.

host_about:
Hallo, liebe/r Interessent! 
Ich bin Edit, eine gebürtige Budapester Lehrerin, seit fast 50 Jahren mit Dieter,  einem echten Wiener, glücklich verheiratet. Wir haben drei Kinder und 8 Enkelkinder, die uns jung und agil erhalten. Seit33 Jahren führe ich die Pension Anzengruber, wo ich vom Island bis zu den Fidschi Inseln  Gäste begrüßen konnte, von denen viele zu Freunden geworden sind. Ich liebe und interessiere mich für die Menschen und mit Ihren mir erzählten Lebensgeschichten und Erzählungen könnte ich schon ein Buch füllen.
Ein gemeinsames Lebensziel von meinem Mann und mir war etwas Altes der Nachwelt zu erhalten. Dieses Ziel konnten wir mit der Rettung der "Alten Villa" verwirklichen, die abgerissen hätte sein sollen. Ich glaube, die Rettung und Renovierung ist uns gut gelungen - sehen Sie sich die Fotos an! :-)
Und die interessante Geschichte der Villa erzähle ich Ihnen gerne, wenn ich auch Sie , als lieben Gast,  begrüßen darf... 
Bis bald! 
Herzlichst  Edit (ohne h:-)

host_about:
Hallo, liebe/r Interessent! 
Ich bin Edit, eine gebürtige Budapester Lehrerin, seit fast 50 Jahren mit Dieter,  einem echten Wiener, glücklich verheiratet. Wir haben drei Kinder und 8 Enkelkinder, die uns jung und agil erhalten. Seit33 Jahren führe ich die Pension Anzengruber, wo ich vom Island bis zu den Fidschi Inseln  Gäste begrüßen konnte, von denen viele zu Freunden geworden sind. Ich liebe und interessiere mich für die Menschen und mit Ihren mir erzählten Lebensgeschichten und Erzählungen könnte ich schon ein Buch füllen.
Ein gemeinsames Lebensziel von meinem Mann und mir war etwas Altes der Nachwelt zu erhalten. Dieses Ziel konnten wir mit der Rettung der "Alten Villa" verwirklichen, die abgerissen hätte sein sollen. Ich glaube, die Rettung und Renovierung ist uns gut gelungen - sehen Sie sich die Fotos an! :-)
Und die interessante Geschichte der Villa erzähle ich Ihnen gerne, wenn ich auch Sie , als lieben Gast,  begrüßen darf... 
Bis bald! 
Herzlichst  Edit (ohne h:-)

Situated between two of Vienna's most famous recreation areas: Donauinsel & Alte Donau its perfect to enjoy outdoor activities.

host_about:
„To travel is our passion and architecture is our profession“

To combine these two aspects - create a design apartment that meets our requirements as travellers and as architects - was our challenge.

The Experiences we have gained in our own extensive travels on all continents and the hospitality we have received from people around the world have motivated us to create an atmosphere in which you enjoy comfort combined with classic design - a convenience to make you feel at home.

We have learned on our journeys is that it all comes down to the people. Hospitality is not related to income and a warm smile is not a question of education. Our wish is to pass on a little of both and hoping you feel like at home away from home.

We would be delighted to personally welcome you as our guest in one of our apartments soon.

Bon Voyage!

name: Himmel im Herzen Wiens
description: This room is a gem over the rooftops of Vienna and spreads real Viennese charm with a lot of love for detail. It is centrally located right next to the 1st district and you can easily reach many famous Viennese sights on foot.
neighborhood_overview: The 8th district, called Josefstadt, is one of the most beautiful areas of Vienna, surrounded by museums and theatres and borders on the 1st district - the immediate center of Vienna. The city of Josefstadt was rebuilt around 1700 after the last Turkish siege in the city. It is a fascinating mix of old and modern - busy during the day and lively at night. A secret tip is the park in the area of the "Altes Krankenhaus" with its many courtyards, in which also a part of the campus of the University of Vienna is located. You can reach many well-known sights such as the Vienna City Hall, the Burgtheater, Stephansplatz and Ringstrasse with the museums on foot. There are several supermarkets and many nice cafes and restaurants around the block.

neighborhood_overview:
The 8th district, called Josefstadt, is one of the most beautiful areas of Vienna, surrounded by museums and theatres and borders on the 1st district - the immediate center of Vienna. The district is a fascinating mix of old and modern - busy during the day and lively at night.

An insider tip is the park in the area of the "Old Hospital" with its many courtyards, in which part of the campus of the University of Vienna is also located. You can walk to many well-known attractions such as Vienna City Hall, Burgtheater, Stephansplatz and Ringstrasse with the museums. There are several supermarkets and many nice cafes and restaurants around the block.
host_about: WELCOME HOME ist mein Motto!  Auf meinen vielen Reisen war ich selber oft genug zu Gast bei Airbnb Hosts und weiss was wichtig ist, um sich auch im Urlaub wohl und zu Hause zu fühlen.  Diese Erfahrung möchte ich gerne an meine Gäste weiter geben und  freuen mich darauf, auch dir einen unvergesslichen Aufenthalt  zu ermöglichen.

neighborhood_overview:
Our accommodation offers an ideal location to explore the treasures and attractions of Vienna. The Heeresgeschichtliche Museum is just 1.3 km away, inviting you to immerse yourself in military history. The impressive Belvedere Castle is at a distance of 1.9 km and impresses with its baroque splendor.

For the lovers of music history, the house of music is only 3.4 km away and offers an interactive journey through the world of sounds. Art enthusiasts should have the Albertina Museum (3.6 km), the Leopold Museum (3.6 km) and the Kunsthistorische Museum (3.7 km) on their list.

The treasures of nature and history await you in the Natural History Museum (3.8 km) and in the Imperial Treasury (3.9 km). A walk to the majestic Hofburg (4 km) and the picturesque Volksgarten Wien (4.1 km) will take you into the royal past of the city.

The property is in the immediate vicinity of the Reumannplatz subway station (only 300 m away) and to the Troststraße subway station
